<div id="wikihead"><h2>Home</h2></div>

<div id="wikicontent"><div class="page"><p>Welcome to the Angband wiki. To edit most pages, you will need to register for an account. <a href="http://rephial.org/wiki/HowToFormat">HowToFormat</a> describes the markup system on this wiki, in case you don&#39;t understand plain text. :)</div><hr /><div class="page"><h3 id="s1_1">Things of interest here:</h3><ul><li><p><b>Angband manual</b><br />A new <a href="http://rephial.org/wiki/UserManual">user manual</a> is under development here. This is currently being rewritten from scratch by James Doyle; sections on Setting Up, Getting Started with and Playing the Game have largely been completed, while the remainder is still essentially Leon Marrick&#39;s work .<p>Also under construction is a basic <a href="http://rephial.org/wiki/PlayersGuide">strategy guide</a>.<li><p><b>Compiling</b><br /><a href="http://rephial.org/wiki/Compiling">Compiling</a> instructions for various platforms.<li><p><b>Resources</b><br />Resources that people may find useful, such as downloadable <a href="http://rephial.org/wiki/AngbandLogo">Angband logos</a>.<li><p><b>Open Source Initiative</b><br />See <a href="http://rephial.org/wiki/OpenSource">OpenSource</a> for the GPL effort. This is now complete - Angband has been available under the GPL since 3.1.1.<li><p><b>Development</b><br />The main development wiki is now at <a href="http://trac.rephial.org/wiki">http://trac.rephial.org/wiki</a> This site still contains an old page of Plans<a href="http://rephial.org/wiki/Plans">?</a> for the game, for interest.</ul></div></div>

